# Quality Rules

- Add or update tests for changed behavior when possible.
- Run relevant checks before finalizing.
- Fail fast on unclear assumptions; document open risks.
- Avoid silent error handling.
- Prefer explicit names and small functions.
- Do not mark a task complete unless verification was attempted.
- If tests are missing, explain what manual checks were performed.
- Keep user-facing error messages clear and actionable.